Alternative letter-case form of Greek (“anal sex”).

verbs.description: greek (third-person singular simple present greeks, present participle greeking, simple past and past participle greeked)

entries.meaning: (transitive, computing) To display a placeholder (instead of text), especially to optimize speed in displaying text that would be too small to read.
(transitive, computing) To fill a template with nonsense text (particularly the Lorem ipsum), so that form can be focused on instead of content.
